      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FABULOUS FLEUR (1) was below best at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth at this track, but was among the placings at this track three back. Good beginner and aided by the inside draw. Meets a moderate line up and rates on top this time. PUDDIN' CAKE (2) turned in a plain performance last time when sixth at this track over 305m (18.51) in a TG1-4W. Placed at her previous run. Has good speed and a low draw is a big help. One of the better chances. RALPH THE RAT (7) was below best at his last start when 8th at Horsham following a win (17.81) at this track two back. The form out of his last race has been franked. Should play a prominent role. STICKY FINGERS (8) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
